		"description": "<p>Starting at 10th level, when you take damage, you&nbsp;can use your reaction to exploit chaos to protect&nbsp;yourself.</p>\n<p>Roll 3d6 and check the individual values of the dice on the following table:</p>\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 100.781px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 22.8083%;\"><col style=\"width: 77.1917%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\"><strong>Result</strong></td>\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\"><strong>Effect</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 33.5938px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 33.5938px;\">distinct values</td>\n<td style=\"height: 33.5938px;\">You reduce the amount of damage by the&nbsp;result of the highest dice, plus your&nbsp;spellcasting modifier (minimum 1).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 33.5938px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 33.5938px;\">2 of a kind</td>\n<td style=\"height: 33.5938px;\">You take half damage, and your assailant&nbsp;takes the other half of the damage.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">3 of a kind</td>\n<td style=\"height: 16.7969px;\">Your assailant takes that damage instead,&nbsp;and you take no damage.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Additionally, you gain temporary hit points equals to the highest die. Those temporary hit points last for 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a short or long rest.</p>",
